.TH "gelic_card_init_chain" 9 "gelic_card_init_chain" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gelic_card_init_chain \- links descriptor chain
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gelic_card_init_chain
.BI "(struct gelic_card *card "  ","
.BI "struct gelic_descr_chain *chain "  ","
.BI "struct gelic_descr *start_descr "  ","
.BI "int no "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "card" 12
card structure
.IP "chain" 12
address of chain
.IP "start_descr" 12
address of descriptor array
.IP "no" 12
number of descriptors
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
we manage a circular list that mirrors the hardware structure,
except that the hardware uses bus addresses.

returns 0 on success, <0 on failure
